HEADWORD: Anthrax vaccine
<hw>An"thrax vac"cine</hw>. <fld>(Veter.)</fld> <def>A fluid vaccine
obtained by growing a bacterium (<spn>Bacillus anthracis</spn>, formerly
<spn>Bacterium anthracis</spn>) in beef broth. It is used to immunize
animals, esp. cattle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anthrenus</ent>⟦br⟧
